job_detail:
Gizmospring is a group of passionate creative innovative product developers with a self-owned state-of-the-art manufacturing facility aiming to improve lifestyles through little innovations.

As a mechanical engineer, you will work with designers, product managers, and cross-functional teams inside Gizmo to lead our process for new products from development to production.

Does this sound exciting to you? You might be the person we're looking for!

★ In this role, you will get to ★
1. Participate in project research and project demand analysis;
2. Conduct mechanical feasibility study from initial ID concepts through sizing analysis, 
    component selection, refinement of design details, assembly and integration, and 
    performance/environment qualification testing
3. Work closely with cross function team such as ID, QA vendor and CMs;
4. Search out materials, and components. Create detailed 3D CAD models, 2D drawing, 
    BOM and specification related to ME for the product;
5. Build prototypes, analyze results of reliability testing, improve the design and bring to 
    production;
6. Work with QA and CMs to complete tooling trial and verification;
7. Responsible for new product mass production introduction and related work.


★ About you ★
- Love solving problems in a fast-paced environment with many moving parts;
- Valuable player, with a focus on teamwork and how we can work better together;
- Fast learner, curious and willing to take risks;
- Able to work with many different projects in parallel;
- Strong collaborator and communicator;
- Comfortable with working with stakeholders in different locations, both local and 
  international;
- Take ownership and accountability for the assigned tasks;
- Can prioritize and ask the right questions.

★ You are expected to have ★
- BS or above, in mechanical engineering with at least 2+ years of hands-on design 
  experience;
- Has manufacturability design capabilities, including 2D and 3D design, BOM, tolerance 
  analysis, tooling release validation, etc.;
- Familiar with PTC Creo;
- Able to effectively collaborate with cross-functional teams and external vendors to 
  achieve product goals;
- Experience in owning a mechanical development effort as a lead engineer;
- Capable of reviewing DFM process for injection, stamping, and casting;
- Can understand and compile FMEA data.

