As an electronic Engineer, you will work with designers, product managers, and cross-functional teams inside Gizmo to lead our process for new products from development to production.

Does this sound exciting to you? You might be the person we're looking for!

★ In this role, you will get to ★
1. Participate in project research and project demand analysis;
2. Responsible for defining electronic hardware and software requirements of new 		 
    products;
3. Responsible for writing design documents, manuals, etc. related to electronic 
    specifications;
4. Compile technical documents related to the project's electronic design;
5. Assist and cooperate to complete product debugging and verification;
6. Responsible for new product mass production introduction and related work.

★ About you ★
-  Love solving problems in a fast-paced environment with many moving parts;
-  Valuable player, with a focus on teamwork and how we can work better together;
-  Able to work with many different projects in parallel;
-  Strong collaborator and communicator;
-  Comfortable with working with stakeholders in different locations, both local and 
   international;
-  Take ownership and accountability for the assigned tasks;
-  Can prioritize and ask the right questions.

★ You are expected to have ★
-  College degree or above, major in electronics;
-  3 years of experience in electronic product development, 
-  Familiar with software such as Altium Designer or Protel99;
-  Experienced with embedded systems, and understand the basic software process and 
   framework;
-  Familiar with mainstream MCU and STM32;
-  Understands signal integrity design, reliability, EMC;
-  Has manufacturability design capabilities;

★ It's great, but not required if you have ★
-  Understands the technology applied to beauty equipment, including radio frequency 
   technology, micro-current technology, and wireless charging technology.
